```

Replace `'your_collection_name'` with the name of your collection and `'field_name'` with the name of the field you want to perform the "like" query on.

By using `isGreaterThanOrEqualTo: substring` and `isLessThanOrEqualTo: substring + '\uf8ff'`, you are effectively performing a range query that matches the substring `"arch_st"`.

This approach works because `'\uf8ff'` is the last possible Unicode character, so the range from `substring` to `substring + '\uf8ff'` covers all possible values that contain `substring` as a substring.

